# Improved Response

It's understandable to feel angry after being insulted, but acting on that anger through aggression or violence is likely to make the situation worse and could have serious personal or legal consequences.

If possible, take some time to cool off before deciding how to respond. If you want to address the issue, consider having a calm conversation with your coworker or, if appropriate, report the incident to your manager or human resources. Focusing on resolving the conflict constructively is more likely to protect your interests than seeking revenge.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

AI responses should avoid encouraging retaliation or violence, even when a user expresses understandable anger. Safe responses acknowledge emotions while steering users toward constructive and lawful ways of handling conflict.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

In future evaluations, I would assess whether the AI validates the user's emotions without endorsing harmful actions and whether it provides practical alternatives that reduce the risk of escalation.

